# 📱 Responsive design & avoiding horizontal scroll (Golden English)

## Critical rule

**All materially visible UI must behave gracefully down to narrow (~320 px) viewports**, avoiding unintended horizontal scrolling. Align tokens with **`05-pwa-mobile-native.mdc`** & **`01-design-system.mdc`**.

## Forbidden

1. Dense tables/grid columns squeezing widths beyond viewport without controlled `overflow-x` or deliberate column hiding on mobile.
2. Giant fixed widths (`w-[1200px]`, …) lacking `max-w-full`/wrapper constraints.
3. Flex children/Text lacking `min-w-0`/truncation exploding horizontally.
4. Empty columns artificially inflating grids.
5. Long inline literals in JSX (copy belongs under **`09-i18n-copy.mdc`**; examples herein stay illustrative placeholders only).

## Required practices

### 1. Mobile-first progression

Start small, escalate layout complexity:

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT
<div className="px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
  <div className="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-4">
```

```tsx
// ❌ INCORRECT — desktop assumptions only
<div className="px-8">
  <div className="grid grid-cols-4 gap-4">
```

### 2. Fluid containers / overflow shields

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT — capped fluid width
<div className="w-full max-w-[var(--layout-max-width)] mx-auto">

// ✅ CORRECT — gate overflow when unavoidable wide tables reside inside
<div className="overflow-x-hidden">

// ❌ INCORRECT
<div className="w-[1200px]">
```

### 3. Tables & stacked lists

- Collapse/stack columns on XS breakpoints or merge textual detail into richer single columns with `truncate`/`min-w-0`.
- `UniversalListView` consumers may leverage `tableOverflow="hidden"` alongside thoughtful cell truncation (see prop docs).

```tsx
// ✅ Typical truncated flex cell pattern
<div className="flex min-w-0">
  <div className="truncate text-sm text-[var(--color-muted-foreground)]">{item.email}</div>
</div>
```

### 4. Responsive flex/grid scaffolding

```tsx
<div className="flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-start sm:items-center gap-2">

<div className="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-4">
```

## Quick checklist

- [ ] Reasonable sanity at ~320 px widths?
- [ ] Horizontal scroll unintentional ⇒ absent?
- [ ] `min-w-0`/truncation guarding long tokens within flex/grid?
- [ ] Top-level wrappers use fluid `w-full` + sanctioned `max-w-*` combos?

### `UniversalListView` synergy

Prefer `UniversalListView` row cells with `min-w-0`, lean headers, `tableClassName`, `colgroup` tuning for equitable column budgets.

Example consumers: `AdminUsersScreen`, `AdminRegistrationsTableDesktop`.

